<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/vars.css" />
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/god.css" />
        <title>Document</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="outer-container">
            <div class="container fade-2s">
                <h1 id="header-name" class="">
                    EPHEMERAL<span class="throb">❦</span>HEART
                </h1>
                <h3 style="margin: 0px">✧༺♡༻✧</h3>

                <nav>
                    <a href="/" class="link">home</a>
                    <a href="/" class="link">about</a>
                    <a href="/" class="link">sasha</a>
                </nav>

                <div class="hard-box">
                    <h2 style="margin-bottom: 0px">Tribunal</h2>
                    <p>
                        Welcome to tribunal, where you will decide the fate of a
                        stranger's anonymous message. The choice is entirely
                        yours, and there are no rules or expectations. No one
                        will know what you choose.
                    </p>
                    <p>Consider the following</p>
                    <h2 style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px">
                        Anonymous message
                    </h2>
                    <p><code><%= postText %></code></p>
                    <h2 style="margin-bottom: 0px">Pass or Burn</h2>
                    <p>
                        This message has been passed and read by
                        <span class="invert"><%= passes %></span>
                        other <% if(passes == 1) { %> person<% } else { %>
                        people<% } %>. Will you
                        <span class="invert">pass it</span>, and allow someone
                        else to read it? Or will you
                        <span class="invert">burn it</span>, and permanently
                        erase it?
                    </p>
                    <form action="/submitMessage" method="POST">
                        <div class="tribunal-form">
                            <label for="pass">Pass:</label>
                            <input
                                type="radio"
                                name="PB"
                                id="pass"
                                value="Pass"
                                required
                            />
                            <div style="width: 40px"></div>
                            <label for="burn">Burn:</label>
                            <input
                                type="radio"
                                name="PB"
                                id="burn"
                                value="Burn"
                            />
                            <input
                                type="hidden"
                                name="token"
                                id="token"
                                value="<%= token %>"
                            />
                        </div>
                        <br />
                        <div class="submit">
                            <input type="submit" value="Submit" />
                        </div>
                    </form>
                    <h2 class="red" style="margin-bottom: 0px">Abuse</h2>
                    <p>
                        <i>
                            There is a
                            <span>zero-tolerance policy</span> regarding hateful
                            speech and spam. Failure to follow this will result
                            in a permanent ban. There are no ban appeals.
                        </i>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <i> Please be normal. Thanks. </i>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
